g.text: Each base Docker Image consists of a Salt Minion which configures and builds the Docker Images. Salt can provide a more powerful toolset vs Docker files for building Images.

g.text: Further testing occurs at this stage. If the build succeeds an Image is published to the test artifact repository. In addition an event should be triggered to notify the source-code repository that it is safe to merge to Master.

g.text: In a testing environment the artifact is deployed along other services to replicate a prod-like environment.

g.text: Additional testing occurs within the test environment to observe performance and to ensure the service works with other deployed services.Upon passing acceptance testing, the Image is then published to a production level repository.
